President Obama delivered a pre-taped message during halftime of the NBA All-Star game in 2009, promoting the importance of community service. He encouraged Americans to visit usaservice.org to find ways to serve in their communities. The message highlighted various ways to make a difference, such as preparing care packages for soldiers, reading to children, and fixing up local basketball courts. President Obama urged everyone to join the NBA in serving others and emphasized the need for hope and opportunity in communities. The complete message can be viewed on whitehouse.gov/blog after the game.